Latin

Etymology

From cornū (“horn”)

Pronunciation

  * (Classical) IPA^(key): /korˈnuː.tus/, [kɔrˈnuː.t̪ʊs]
  * (Ecclesiastical) IPA^(key): /korˈnu.tus/, [kɔrˈnuː.t̪us]

Adjective

cornūtus (feminine cornūta, neuter cornūtum); first/second-declension adjective

 1. horned, having horns.
 2. cuckolded

